Read files
Merge the training and the test sets to create one data set.
Column bind files to get the complete table for test observations 
Keep only necessary columns, Subject, Activity and columns containing mean in their description 
Add the Activity for activity type to produce the final test data for observations
Extracts only the measurements on the mean and standard deviation for each measurement.
Uses descriptive activity names to name the activities in the data set
Appropriately labels the data set with descriptive variable names.
From the data set in step 4, creates a second, independent tidy data set with the average of each variable for each activity and each subject.
Write out to txt file the tidy data set in the Data folder
